A Herediano player was reportedly left requiring hospital treatment after an off-the-ball kick to the head during the CONCAFAF Champions League semi-final between the Costa Rican club and Club America.

The feisty game descended into a mass brawl lasting five minutes after Club America midfielder Michael Arroyo left Herediano's Cristhiam Lagos on the floor with a nasty tackle in the 24th minute.

However, while players argued the referee missed what is believed to have been an unintentional but full blooded kick at Lagos' head by Club America defender Paolo Goltz in an effort to clear the ball from near the prone striker.

