The Costa Rica side went on to win the first leg tie 3-0 after making use of their numerical advantage with two goals from Esteban Ramírez and a late third from Lagos' replacement Hansen on 82minutes.

The return leg for a place in the final will take place at the Azteca Stadium on April 8.

